    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="884"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15064.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Am informed that several chiefs now acting with Zapata in the event of rupture
                    will side with Garza. My short acquaintance with the latter impressed me most
                    favorably. He was very friendly to the United States. He appears to be one of
                    the fairest characters which have come up out of the revolution. Foreigners fear
                    that the Zapatistas will kill him before they are through. The Carranzistas <pb
                        facs="0808" n="692" xml:id="pg_692"/> dislike him because he has been a
                    strong Villista. There would be no place for him in their triumph. His
                    assassination would be a great loss and a great pity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
